  <section>
    <h2>Selectable rows</h2>
    <p>Put a <code>.checkbox</code> in the first column to let people pick rows. The header checkbox is the bulk toggle; flip <code>data-state="active"</code> on the row to mark it selected. The <code>data-demo-select-rows</code> hook on the table wires the live behavior.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <table class="table table--hover table--align-middle" data-demo-select-rows>
      <thead class="table__head--alt">
        <tr>
          <th scope="col" style="width: 1rem;">
            <input class="checkbox" type="checkbox" aria-label="Select all subscribers" />
          </th>
          <th scope="col">Email</th>
          <th scope="col">Source</th>
          <th scope="col">Subscribed</th>
          <th scope="col">Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><input class="checkbox" type="checkbox" aria-label="Select maya@acme.co" /></td>
          <td>maya@acme.co</td>
          <td>Landing page</td>
          <td>Jun 02</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge--soft badge--success">Confirmed</span></td>
